annotation.TEXT: Hello, and welcome back to EVW! Today, I'm going to revisit some levels to check out various things that I didn't see earlier. Thanks go to everyone who helped point out many of these!
Yes, this is where I want to be. Now, let's not stupidly open one of the ? blocks!
Lava is not deadly to Buzzy, but most likely deadly to me!
There's this dark block here, but I don't think there's anything special about it.
Hmm... Can I glitch it?
This looks tricky...
Continuing on with the level...
Okay, I'm in another new place... maybe.
Actually, I had plenty of time. There's a red Yoshi egg. Hmm... You know what?
Actually, nothing... No matter what I tried, I couldn't find any insanity effects at that door. However, the next door, after midpoint, is a different story...
...I can avoid warping to that vertical area and keep going right!
A wall, but I can easily jump over it.
Uh, oh... This can't be good...
Remember this place? After the fans got turned on, I was all too eager to enter this door over here...
What's up here?
"No Yoshis allowed"? Screw that! I'll bring Yoshi wherever I want, and this hack can't stop me!
Nuts...
And finally, Yoshi n Berry. I was informed that there is indeed an alternate path here, and it's near the beginning, so fast-forwarding shouldn't be necessary.
I found... a trap that took little effort to fall into! D'oh! This place should've had a ceiling installed... (*Rewind*)
Okay, I think this is the pipe that I want. (Also, yay for P-switch glitches!)
This is just like an earlier area in the level, except there are no sprites, and a few of the floating coins don't have an invisible ledge beneath them.
So that's what this stuff that I saw up here in the non-eversed version was for...
Okay, back in this vertical passageway, I remember going up and dying to a fuzzy in a note block filled area. Let's explore more of that route now.
Everse!
Huh? There's a ceiling up there? Well, there's something solid up there. Whatever.
There's where I'll need the P-switch.
GAAAMMME!!!
I can't collect them! NOOOOO!!!!!
Finally! Okay, now that I'm at the end, it's safe to open a ? block if I want.
Now, at the end here, there's no door. But, that's okay, because I'm sure falling into a pit will warp me back to the "sane" world...
WAAAAHHH!!! Oh, I'm still alive. Okay, that was a good one!
Ow... I'm okay.
And that's the end, but I wonder about something... (*Uses rewind*)
Okay, so let me quickly get back to that other door...
Ooh, suddenly I'm in castle town, or something.
Now this definitely looks familiar! It's too bad that the non-eversed version of this room has no way out besides suicide (or rewinds!) if you enter it.
Nothing really interesting to the right, so I'll go left.

Now, if you just keep running to the right, you'll eventually fall into a pit at some point, and then you'll warp back to the "sane" world. However, if you jump over the pit that you'd fall into, you can keep going...
Aha! Pressing up here leads to gold!
Hi, Yoshi!
What the? Why did that first Sparky not get hit by the shell at first? More sprite slot anomalies?
Okay, new area. I've never been here before...
So, I'm guessing what's supposed to happen is that the player finds that he can walk on air, then just runs to the right, and eventually falls into a pit and warps, like this.
I couldn't find any more insanity effects here, so I figure I'll show this room again.
However, otherwise, it's pretty much identical, so I think I'll fast-forward most of this room.
Note: Rewinds were used at each door in an effort to get different results.
I never did see a pink "edible" berry or a brown "yummy" berry... I guess those berries were lies...
Umm... That lava is seriously screwed up...
Lucky stomp there!
Now, at this point, if I don't jump too high...
Actually, though, that's good, because there's another insanity effect that I found at the door just after midpoint.
Okay, so I take it that the green berries are like moving platforms?
Huh? Oh, I can walk on air. Nice!
Now we've got dark Buzzies. Yay.
COINS!!!! YAY!!! ...Wait, what?
Loss of Sanity... I've been told of a bunch of insanity effects that I haven't seen yet, so let's take a look!
I never did use that P-switch...
Pipe's a no go.
Oh, this place is different, and it's got a reddish color scheme. But, what's the gimmick?
Yes, I have to jump when the ? block dips here. Otherwise, I die.
My guess is that the green berries are actually goombas walking on enemy-only blocks.
No, they're destroyable! So, they're actually enemies!
Let's see what could happen here...
Maybe if I fall back down and duck-jump into the wind...
MOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOONNNNNNNNNNNNNN!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!
I wonder if there's solid ground down there... Well, I don't think I want to take a chance finding out!
Up next is Gust Temple. When I looked over my footage from before, I realized that I didn't explore one section near the end of the level, so I'll just cut to that area.
Insert brain here.
I see a warp down there, but it looks very tricky to reach!
Ooh, dark Spinies, almost like in the Flopside Pit of 100 Trials, except these things don't seem to be any stronger than their normal counterparts...
Yeah, that would've been too easy.
Moving along...
Whoops! Bye, Mario! To be continued...
Nuts... If only I was super...
Oh, this place is new.
Alright, and up here we find a MOOOOONNN!!! However, there's nothing else of interest up here, so I'd have to enter that door below to proceed with the level anyway.
Oh, an enemy? Well, I can spin jump off of it, and I'm guessing normal jumping on it would just hurt me.
Press X to continue.
And that's a goal, so let's go back to that Thwomp and Yoshi coin I told you to remember earlier.
And that's it for Mario's Saga, so next will be... Infection.
Hi, Toad! "Touch nothing"? Screw that! I'll touch whatever I feel like!
Okay, remember this Thwomp and Yoshi coin for later.
Death by insanity...

By the way, I did use a little bit of tool-assistance with the level revisiting. I don't want to end up taking forever just to get through this room just because I barely clipped a lava column or something (which did happen a few times)!
Yeah, you can enter that pipe down there and it also leads to the goal! So, there's no real need to stay on the upper level towards the end of that room!
Yikes! This looks insane! Okay, here goes...
And we end up back in this area. So, I guess I'm done revisiting the levels! Next time, I take on the Source of Variety!
Yeah, I'm definitely going to need all three blocks.
I'm wondering if these dark whatchamacallits are slide-killable, but I'd need to find one that's close enough to a slope first.
Come on. I know I can land on that ledge!
I wonder what determines whether "hyper avoid" will send me left or right...
Since I wasn't supposed to have Yoshi here in the first place... Bye, Yoshi! I'll just work with the baby red Yoshi instead.
Also, we get our first glimpse of the "mobile" green berries here.

Next let's revisit Mario's Saga. I was told (and I kind of figured this myself) that I didn't take the intended path in the second half, so I'm going to go back and refrain from making that 6-tile high jump that I made before.
Fortunately, I didn't really have to go through all that crap!
Now, I was told that there's a coin room that can be accessed from the "good" first Toad room, so I'll just speed through the level and get to that point...
From what I can tell, you can't get two insanity effects in a row at the same door, so you'd need to exit and reenter the level (or rewind!) for a chance at seeing something different.

So, at the end of the bottom corridor, you get warped up here. I'm pretty sure if you slam into the side of a vertical pipe, you'll die, but I managed to avoid them all and not fall down on my first try!
MOOOOOONNN!!! Gulp!
Why these custom boost blocks were used instead of ordinary note blocks is beyond me...
I guess that's a reset pipe.
Hi, Yoshi! Now, I've got to be careful when feeding him. I wouldn't want him to eat a parakoopa that's vital to my survival!
And exiting that room just leads here. This time, however, I don't have to reset the game to go to the next level, thanks to the side exit!
Oh, I can totally break the level here! But, you know what? I think I'll just play it normally.
There we go! (Hmm.. that seemed familiar.)
Oh, yeah. Make sure you don't get pushed into this tiny dead end here, or you'll die (as I demonstrate here).
Okay, now for the hyper-speed second half, the intended way! (I think...)

And that warp just leads here. Okay, I think I've had enough of Shaded Volcano. I probably missed something somewhere, but I don't care. I've already spent nearly half the video revisiting this one level, and this is a pretty long video for me, too!
Let's start with Shaded Volcano. Now, this level is very complex, and I know there are routes that I didn't see the entirety of.
However, I overlooked that fact that I could continue upwards here, so let's check out what's up here!
I got lucky there, and now my red Yoshi is big and strong!
Yes! WHOA!!!
I remember one path that had three ? blocks floating to the left that I died very early in, and I never explored it again. Let's see if I can remember where it was...
Yeah, this is definitely a dark version of the starting room.
Too bad the spiders aren't edible, but the red berries are!
Yay, free life! But, it doesn't look like I can do much else up here... except maybe jump over the pipe! Can I enter that pipe?

However, I think Snifit and Aquamentus didn't take into account the possibility of the player jumping over that pit, or maybe they did, seeing how a few invisible ledges, all sprites, and the exit door were removed. Who knows?
Oh, don't mind me. I'm just idiotically running into a ghost.
Looks like it's a race situation, so I'd better hustle here!
How long is this place?
There sure are a lot of coins...
Nope. Let's see what else I can find here...
Was I supposed to stay on the upper level? Probably, but it's only a 6-tile high jump to get back up there, so...
And as far as I can tell, that's the last of the insanity effects that I didn't find the first time. However, if there are more, let me know!
Huzzah! (Maybe this could've worked at the "No Yoshi" sign near the end of the level too, but I couldn't get Yoshi across the pit beyond that one.)
